        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_æǧnæg" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>æǧnæg</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>застежка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>clasp</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пуговица</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>button</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>rīwy ʽǧnæǵytæ qazync st’alytaw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>застежки на груди играют, как звезды</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>clasps on chest sparkle like stars</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ængom cærūt, æǧnæg æmæ sæxtæg k˳yd cærync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>живите дружно, как живут пуговица и петля</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>live together like a button and a buttonhole</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ūj bæsty wal dæ æǧnæǵytæ æværyn sах˳уr ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лучше бы ты научился застегивать свои пуговицы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>you'd better learn how to button up</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восстанавливаем в %i*æx-mæg%i, %i*ærx-næg%i, где %i-næg%i —
                    суффиксальное (из %i-na%i + %ika%i), как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærnæg"
                    />, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īwnæg"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ægæjnæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tawnæg"/> и др.
                    Элемент %iæx-%i, %iærx-%i со значением ‘скрепление’, ‘скреплять’ и пр.
                        (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*ark-</w></mentioned>) мы находим еще в следующих словах: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘запирать’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxtong"
                    /> ‘подпруга’ и д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxu"/> ‘плотно замкнутый’,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> | %iærxængæ%i ‘сустав’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_arx"/> ‘сук’ и, может быть, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arkʼaw"/> ‘клещи’. Для семантического ряда ‘застежка’ — ‘сук’
                    — ‘клещи’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>giri</w>
                        <gloss><q>застежка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>узел</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сук</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>gīra</w>
                        <gloss><q>клещи</q></gloss></mentioned>. См. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxkænyn"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">We reconstruct it as %i*æx-mæg%i, %i*ærx-næg%i, where %i-næg%i
                    is a suffix (from %i-na%i + %ika%i), like in <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xærnæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īwnæg"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ægæjnæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tawnæg"/>
                    etc. The element %iæx-%i, %iærx-%i with the meaning ‘fastening’, ‘fasten’ etc.
                        (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*ark-</w></mentioned>) we can find in other words: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘lock’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxtong"/>
                    ‘girth’ and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxu"/> ‘tightly closed’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> | %iærxængæ%i ‘joint’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arx"/> ‘bough’ and, perhaps, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arkʼaw"/> ‘pliers’. For the semantic chain ‘clasp’ — ‘bough’
                    — ‘pliers’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>giri</w>
                        <gloss><q>clasp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>knot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bough</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>gīra</w>
                        <gloss><q>pliers</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxkænyn"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
